caption: Great food, excellent service! Ordered takeout for Daughter's 18th birthday and couldn't have been more pleased. Excellent service, great staff! Manager Dana was very helpful and definitely had her eye on every detail.  Look forward to ordering from there again soon.

Zero seasoning and not enough sauce. Also the “garlic bread” was just sub bread with a slab of cheese on top. Ordered chicken Alfredo, spicy chicken sausage casserole and garlic bread. Worst $45 ever spent!
Awesome like always

The food here was not good, especially for the price.  I ordered the Veal Piccata, garlic bread and crab cakes.  My wife ordered the Crab Cakes with Angel hair and my daughter had Chicken Parm.  The veal was bland and tasted like it was boiled, and the sauce that it came in was watery and generally flavorless.  The garlic bread was completely uninspired, it practically looked like Kroger rolls baked with a thin slice of mozzarella, drizzled with crushed garlic mixed into olive oil.  The crab cakes tasted similar to baby powder.  My wife said that, for the most part, the calamari was good, but agreed on the taste of the crab cakes and commented that her spaghetti was bland, the broccoli was crunchy and the sauce tasted like watered-down tomato paste straight from the can. My daughter commented that the chicken parm tasted like dry tomato paste and burnt mozzarella (there was no flavour to the chicken). This food is not worth the price tag it came with.  It was a $100+ meal.  I will be disposing of most of it as I cannot finish it for how poor it tastes and do not want to imagine its flavour when re-heated.  No stars.  This place needs Gordon Ramsay.  Will never order from here again.  My food was pictured below.
Great place to eat! Huge servings and friendly staff!
Just ordered the Chicken Saltimbocca via Ubereats.  The chicken was STALE you know that plastic taste? Yea disgusting will never order again
Great food!  My family and I come hear what every year

What happened to Dominick's? This used to be a classy restaurant with quality service and food. Arrived at 5:15 and we were seated in the very back corner of the restaurant near a stack of unused chairs and the freezing back door. It was table 601, and we know this because someone had written all of the table numbers in magic marker on the tablecloths. It was absolutely freezing in the restaurant. Everyone in our section ate with their coats on because it was so cold. It took almost an hour and a half for our food to be served. We skipped desserts that we were looking forward to because it took so long. It looked like teenagers were running the restaurant. The servers weren't dressed nicely at all - just random tshirts. Disappointed it has gone so downhill. Very pricey for the experience.
Incredible manicotti!
My husband & I love this place. Our favorite Italian restaurant ever. Great food & service.
Food is always fresh & flavorful.
Great experience - professional and courteous staff.
The servings are enormous but I was disappointed on the taste.  Very friendly staff nice atmosphere.

I arrived at 8:15pm. I ordered the Chicken Piccata with Angel Hair Pasta. I was disappointed in the presentation of the Chicken Piccata. I thought I was being served soup. My food was cold and the noodles was clumpy. I asked about the bread that you are normally served, I was told they threw all the bread out.  The manager did come and ask me how my meal was. I was honest and told her I had better. I shared with her how disappointed I was with my meal. She offer to comp me half price. I told her no thank you. I want to pay full price for my meal. Will I return? No thank you.  As I was waiting for my check, the guest a few tables down was offered black pepper and bread, how ironic.
Excellent food with large portions. Friendly staff

My second time going and I must say beside the good drinks that were made for me my first time it has been a disappointment.  Chicken taste like it was re heated..and then they through mushroom soup on top. Sorry but ill pass
The food was fabulous!

We held a rehearsal dinner Saturday night at Dominick's. The food was excellent and the service was very good as well. Austin did a great job handling our big crowd and we appreciated his efforts and concern about getting it right. Very good experience and we thank Dominick's for everything they did to make the event so enjoyable.
Soooo much garlic!

Real Italian Food!  Wow, the fresh ingredients in these simple but complex tastes is memorable.  The portions are meant to share as the half portion is more than enough for one.  You will want to take your left overs so you can enjoy one more taste the next day.  When I eat lighter the Sicialian Salad is very satisfying.
Food was ok service was great, very friendly staff.
Please... Order the HALF option! So Delicious!
Delicious food, Friend staffs with a smile

First time eating here. We had Mushroom Ravioli, Chicken Carbonara (sp?)  Cheese Ravioli and Spicy Chicken and Sausage...only food left on anyone's plate was the spicy one...a little too spicy. Half size plates were perfect,  full size were HUGE! Highly recommended!
The food was good the service was great made for a great evening
Our waiter Dominick was awesome! He made sure our drinks were always full and was cutting up with us. The food was amazing!

Tonight we happened to walk into what was suppose to be a fine Italian restaurant. It is apparent that this restaurant lacks the understanding of Italian food. I mean by saying -no taste in the marinara sauce ( it might have as well been ketchup salt free).  The stuffed mushroom was undercooked and lack flavor. The only thing fresh on it was the basil. The salad was waiting for a customer all day long. The spaghetti I couldn’t wait to get to this one .... string cheese has more flavor and flexibility. Talk about crumble in your mouth. I thought it was Alka-Seltzer!!! - Their are no words to describe the veal except for dry. No moisture at all in the meat!! Pieces of toast have more moisture in it. We spent $60 and had to get food  elsewhere. If I could give it zero stars I would.

The first time I went there the food was marvelous. I went there two times after ordered the same thing I ordered the first time .And I was highly disappointed. Being a chef I expect my meal to taste the same every time especially when I'm getting the same thing . 🤢 I ordered the chicken carbonara. Like I said the first visit the food was delicious. The second two times the food didn't taste the same 🤷

The location is great in downtown Lawrenceville. The inside is very nice.  Staff was friendly had a great waiter.  The bread appetizer was good it was better with a side of marinara sauce . I'm not much of a pasta person but my entrée with the tiger shrimp was delicious.  The sauce and cheese is amazing.  You should definitely try it . The manger or owner came over and checked in us very nice good conversation . Our entrée were half size not full . Definitely will be back.
Great portions super friendly staff
Excellent food with a vast wine menu selection.

Big portions. I liked the atmosphere. It is priced as a fancier place without the fancier service.  I feel like this place is having an identity crisis. It wants to be fancy, but also wants to attract people who expect huge portions and a menu on the wall. The garlic bread sits in a pool of oil, but you get cloth napkins and a tablecloth.  Antipasto comes with sliced olives instead of whole. Literally only 4 slices of meat wrapped around narrow pieces of cheese.  I personally didn't like the spaghetti. I also don't like to remove my straw so the server can go refill the same glass with Coke.
Giant portions. Friendly staff. Awesome food.
Wonderful birthday dinner and celebration. Food was excellent. Veal a bit tough one piece. Service fantastic.
One of my favorite date night spots! Thanks for always serving the most amazing Italian food.

The pasta was HORRIBLE! The sauce was bitter and lacked any flavoring. And it was extremely overpriced for the quality. I couldn't be more serious about the following statement: A jar of Rao's Arrabiata sauce and a package of angel hair pasta would have been way better(and cheaper.) If they brought that out to me, I would have accepted that over what I got. I would give no stars if I could.
The food was delicious, and the service was exceptional!  Tifney went over and beyond to make sure we were comfortable.
We go every Saturday night!  Ask for Dana and have her make you an Italian margarita!
I literally cried at the table, it was so delicious. I felt like I was at a dinner with my late grandparents again. thank you. I will return with my mother.
This was my first visit, there Italian  food is delicious and fresh. The bartender made me feel welcome and she threw in a free dessert...please try there lasagna  you will not be disappointed
The food is wayyyy over priced. I was asked to pay $108 for food that I didn’t eat because it was terrible. I walked out paying $66 for 2 people and we didn’t eat anything.

The food is always good and they give you a huge pile of it......seriously....the half portions are enough for two people.  I always want to order a full portion just to see what kind of thanksgiving platter it has to come out on...hahahaha

(Translated by Google) Dominick's is probably one of my favorite spots in Downtown Lawrenceville! Their chicken parmigiana is probably the juiciest one I've had in a while.  We ordered the chicken parmigiana, and the chicken Alfredo. The parmigiana is served with spaghetti topped with marinara, and mozzarella baked to melty perfection. I can't describe how much I love this dish.  The service was outstanding! There was only one server on a full house for lunch time and he still manage to provide excellent costumer service.  If you're in the area give this place a try. There's plenty of parking around Downtown.  SPANISH  Dominick is probably one of my favorite places in downtown Lawrenceville! Their parmesan chicken is probably the juiciest I've had in a long time.  We ordered the chicken parmigiana and the chicken Alfredo. Parmesan served with spaghetti topped with marinara and perfectly baked mozzarella. I cannot describe how much I love this dish.  The service was excellent! There was only one waiter in a full house for lunch and he still managed to provide excellent customer service.  If you are in the area, try this place. There is a lot of parking around the center.  (Original) Dominick's is probably one of my favorite spots in Downtown Lawrenceville! Their chicken parmigiana is probably the juiciest one I've had in a while.  We ordered the chicken parmigiana, and the chicken Alfredo. The parmigiana is served with spaghetti topped with marinara, and mozzarella baked to melty perfection. I can't describe how much I love this dish.  The service was outstanding! There was only one server on a full house for lunch time and he still manage to provide excellent costumer service.  If you're in the area give this place a try. There's plenty of parking around Downtown.  ESPAÑOL  Dominick es probablemente uno de mis lugares favoritos en el centro de Lawrenceville! Su pollo a la parmesana es probablemente el más jugoso que he probado en mucho tiempo.  Pedimos el pollo a la parmesana y el pollo Alfredo. La parmesana se sirve con espagueti cubierto con marinara y mozzarella horneada a la perfección. No puedo describir cuánto amo este plato.  El servicio fue excelente! Solo había un mesero en una casa llena para la hora del almuerzo y todavía se las arreglo para proporcionar un excelente servicio al cliente.  Si estás en la zona, prueba este lugar. Hay mucho estacionamiento alrededor del centro.

I had never been to a Dominick's location before. My wife suggested it for our anniversary. Food was amazing, service was spot on and all while taking safety precautions.during this time. Definitely will be going back!
loved dominicks. loved dana even more!
The food was great. We will definitely be back. The portion size, is very very generous. Everyone brought home at least half their food.  Staff was friendly as well.

We have never had a bad meal at Dominick's! The gorgonzola salad and garlic cheese bread are always fresh and delicious! The staff is always pleasant and attentive and we are continually impressed with the manager Dana- she is always so professional and attentive!

We always have a wonderful experience at Dominick's. The service and food are incredible and the portion sizes are huge so we always have leftovers for the next day! And we love Dana-  she is always pleasant and professional!
My wife and I dined at Dominick’s Lawrenceville. Chance was a great server and Dana was terrific. She made great wine selections and checked on us several times. We are so happy they have reopened

Our experience last night reminded us of the show kitchen nightmares.  We should have known to leave when there was a big nasty smudge of food on the menu during a pandemic.  The fried food was so brown it was almost black - probably old oil.  The bolognese sauce looked like vomit.  The chicken on the carbonara was old and the dish had no flavor.  The lady at the bar appeared to be the owner.  She failed to greet us as we came or left even though the restaurant was empty.  We didn't eat our food or ask for to-go containers but she failed to notice or care. The only positive was that the waitstaff were friendly.

I realize it is Mother’s Day, but you should be prepared for this event, especially in this environment. My son has been waiting for over two hours for food. I will not be back. Thank you to my wonderful children who try to do something nice and were insulted by Dominicks.
Omg!  This is some amazing Italian food

Got take out 4/19/20 first the mel came without bread then when we got home the food was cold and I only live 5 minutes away the lasagna the cheese was dry and cheese was completely burned from bottom

1st. Time going to this place. Probably won't go back. They are way over priced, $24 for two small, mostly bread crumbs, "Crab Cakes" on top of pasta. I had to ask for the Bread that should come before your meal. The food was brought to the table, then we had to ask someone else for Silverware, to eat it. It wasn't completely terrible. It wasn't that great either.
great place to eat. The chicken scallopini is outstanding, my wife had Penne casserole with tiger shrimp. wait staff is superb!!!
Good food and service at a reasonable price
The bread is delicious. The wine is tasty. Will definitely go back.
The food and service were impeccable!  Would definitely recommend. My husband and I celebrated Valentine's Day dinner at Dominick's. The ambiance was perfect!

Unfortunately it just wasn't very good especially for the price. The Chicken tasted like it was a frozen chicken breast they threw in a pan till it was slightly warm. The best part of the dish was the twig of rosemary they threw on the top. At least that part was fresh.

Food as usual was fantastic. Service was mediocre, not due to the waitress, but the fact that she was severely overloaded with big parties and virtually no backup. That's a management issue, not a server issue. It certainly put a damper on the birthday we were celebrating.

We decided to give them a try instead of our usual Italian joint in Suwanee and we shouldn’t have! :( I had the chicken Marsala and the sauce was very watered down. The chicken was that cheap chicken you get at Chinese places and it was way too overpriced for not quality chicken. I saved the other half of the chicken and gave it to my cats as a treat the next day (too expensive to trash but not good enough for me to eat)! My partner had the baked ziti and the sauce was toooo sweet. They ran out of bread (how?) so we had to buy bread as an appetizer (no free bread but bread to buy lol)!  The staff are all very nice! But we won’t be coming back.

Very bad customer service due to misinformed employees.  You'll get different information from each one, there is definitely a lack of communication amongst them and management.  However, the lasagna was great.  But the garlic bread was sitting in too much butter.
Absolutely wonderful restaurant! Delicious food and a cozy atmosphere.

When we entered the restaurant last night, we were greeted with the delicious aromas of Italian cuisine!  We had reservations so we were seated quickly.  Our server was Dan and he was very attentive and knowledgeable of their extensive menu!  Per his recommendation, we ordered the lasagna and garlic cheese bread with a bottle of red wine!  Everything was yummy and served hot.  We left with enough for lunch today!  Would definitely go back and try something different the next time!  Sad wewaited so long to try Dominick's!  Would highly recommend this restaurant!
What a great place to enjoy a meal with  family and friends!  Kevin did an outstanding job taking care of us!  The food is amazing!
Overrated. Portions are huge but taste is nothing special. Ton of sauce that you can't even taste the real ingredients. Mediocre at best

I have to say I am surprised I had to give this place anything other than 5 stars but the last time we went the food was SOO basic that it really was just blah. We went with a big group and had the entire place to ourselves. They had catering style food but nearly everything was plain and not much spice. I remembered Dominick's as being really good back when I lived closer. Not sure if this was a bad night or if the place has gone downhill.

This is a place we have been going to for a while. This place is pricey just like any Italian food place though why nobody knows. There food used to be great with great portion sizes. Recently they had a bad score and we wanted to try it after that. The food there is average at the best. What I had ordered had too much salt and the other entree had a sauce that was too soupy. Service was great but I think as we have seen over the years their quality has gone down from great to average food. Maybe I feel it happens to places as they become popular, they become lax and that is not healthy in the long run.
Great food. Friendly staff.
horrible service even during slow times. Food is just ok and even that’s pushing it. Personally I never plan on stepping foot in that place again.
Huge portions, so definitely only go for the half portion of dishes (and even then you'll have left overs!). Great food and great service.
Such wonderful high-quality food. They give you a ton for a serving.
Authentic Italian cuisine.  Great menu variety.
Great place to go on a date , wonderful service and people
I really like their food and service, good location next to my apartment. The employees are always very welcoming. I highly recommend this place.

-The appetizer and entrees were good -The alcoholic drinks are terrible. I had to send back my wine because it tasted like it came from an$8 bottle of wine that has been left open for a few days. The mixed drink I swapped it out for was no better, so avoid those at all costs.  We had the half portions of the lasagna and chicken parmigiana and it was more than enough to fill up two people. The lasagna was not what I was expecting look wise but the taste was pretty good. The chicken piece I had was what can be expected of chicken parmigiana, although my fiancé said his piece was very tough to eat. The best part of our meal was the appetizer. It was delicious and something new to try.  We parked on the side of the building off the street and the walk wasn’t too bad. The restaurant was so cold we had to leave our jackets on during dinner. It had the feel of a pub more so than an Italian restaurant. We had two servers which was a little frustrating because one would ask what we needed then never  come back.  Overall I would say it’s definitely worth checking out if you’ve never been. Probably won’t be back though.
Excellent food
Large portions and tasty!
Great food and ambience for our staff Christmas Dinner. We will be back.
Always a great meal! I highly recommend it!
Excellent service and great food
We enjoyed an excellent meal there.
Excellent Italian food. Huge portions. Great service.
Food is very good, portions are large, service is usually very good, and atmosphere is warm and cozy.
Love the food and really good service
Best salads❤❤❤
Food was great, service lacked.
Good Salads! Main food not exceptional. A bit expensive and perhaps over-rated?
GREAT food , Great atmosphere,  Awesome Staff!! I love it!
I've been enjoying Dominick's since the 90's & I've never had a bad meal there, always good food & service.

The service is impeccable and the servers a re very knowledgeable of their menu. Presentation was great. I had the shrimp scampi and it wasn't the best I've ever had. With that being said, I would go back and I would recommend. It's in the heart of downtown Lawrenceville which makes for a nice date night.

Service is polite and friendly, but slow and at times inattentive.  It took about 5 minutes to flag someone down after we got our food to send my husband's plate back.  His food was cold. The second plate was a little warmer but not hot, so that was pretty disappointing.  The calamari and my stuffed pork chop were very good, though. We agreed that we probably just caught them on an off day, and will try them again.
Very good pasta dish and very pleasant staff. Portion was very large and worth bringing home for leftovers.

The gentleman that waited on our table was  Austin he was Amazing. Austin took his time to explain the menu to some of the guests in our party whom have never visited  Dominick before. He was a great server
Never a bad meal. Always good.
Very good food and staff was helpful and friendly. Prices were good for the amount of the good food you got.
Very authentic Italian restaurant. Great food, good atmosphere.
Very good Italian restaurant!!!

We've had food from here twice. Four different entrees all together... The food was overcooked and greasy. As a former cook, I can tell they re heated a dead piece of chicken in the microwave and then put some cheese on it.. and cooked it even longer!!!! I would only recommend the pasta, thankfully they didn't mess up that part of our order... Both times.  I truly wish it was better because we we've heard good reviews in the past, I guess we got  food when the kitchen was  trying to rush home or something. Even my boss said it's not as good as it use to be..  We will definitely not be eating here again, and I will be disencourage people to visit Dominick's.  Sorry Dominick's.
Good people
Spinach salad was superb! Lasagna was delish! The waitress was very nice (& pretty). VERY pleased with our dinner!!
Great food fast service
Omg the food was so good and our waiter Dan was the best. Make sure you request him.
Nice quiet very intimate for a lunch date.
Adriane was fantastic !!
It was truly amazing! It was my family's first time and definitely we'll be back.
We total enjoyed this place the food was great  the waiter Alex was wonderful he had great customer service. I also have to say thank you to the manager Dana who were was very attentive.

Alexander was our server and he was fabulous. Literally said yes to every single thing my family asked for. The balsamic dressing was amazing so I was happy before the main course made it our table. Family style serving of the large portions made it affordable and fine dining at the same time. Highly recommend and we will be back!!
Very pricey but good. HUGE portions, nice ambiance.
Friendly staff and a great place for a group meeting
Loved my dish. Great service from Dan
Fantastic service! Food was amazing and the portion sizes are huge! Definitely recommend!

GOOD Staff. GREAT Food. A bit cramped for seating. Extremely Filling Portion Sizes👍. Told the server it was our anniversary but he did not acknowledge it at all. Not even a simple "Happy Anniversary" response. Will definitely return though but not before trying out the ribs at the restaurant across the street.
Portions are HUGE.  Maybe split a meal to save room for dessert.

I had a Very Friendly waitress/bartender.  Food was good and portions are LARGE! Half servings can feed 2 adults easily.  Prices are higher end, 1 app, 1 main dish (mid-priced for the establishment) and a desert was aprox $50.00 for 1 person.  Environment had a warm setting, not too large with a full bar. Good place for a quiet night out with your sweetheart OR family & Friends.
HUGE portions. Great family style meal. Excellent service. Fairly priced.
Food was delicious. Really good service

Take-out packaging is abysmally thin, always extremely hot with the only way to hold it is with the bag handle, which is weighted down by the 30 pounds of food they stack into one single bag. When you say the customers complain, the staff laughs 🤷🏻‍♂️
Excellent food excellent service a must see in Lawrenceville.
Delicious!  10 star service!

This place is awesome! I've been several times and each time has been great. The salads are delicious and huge! Jeni is a fantastic server...nice, funny, quick and knowledgeable! I will definitely be back.

Just moved to Lawrenceville 2 days ago and love Italian food. Hoping we found our new spot but unfortunately service turned us off. Waited 10 minutes for our server to greet us and ask for drink order. Placed appetizer order with drinks and they came out quickly. Only issue is we had to wave down the waiter to order food AFTER we finished our appetizer. Once food came out it was placed on the wrong table in front of other patrons at the table next to us. One of the people at that table caught it and said this isn't ours after 3 of the entrees were already on the table. Guy picks them up off their table then places them in front of us and walks off. Now we had our entrees but nothing to drink bc our waiter has been MIA since taking our order. Ate a quarter of my meal with nothing to drink. Look up and finally find him in a wait room behind the bar on his cell phone texting and laughing. Food was delicious and huge portions but with the lack of service it's hard to justify going back. 2 apps, 4 entrees, and a bottle of wine. Not exactly cheap which is fine but I expect much better service for a place like this. 3 stars bc the food was great.
Great spot and Good Food. Portions are enough to share.
Caesar salad is always a safe bet
Great for families and groups.

Everything we had was AMAZINGGG!! And the portion size was PHENOMENAL!!! We all got half sizes and ended up taking half of that home!  The flavors were on point! Love a place who's not afraid of a little salt.
Great food, private room and service
5.0 All day long. Great menu, and MY GOD the amount of food you get is amazing. Order a Full size meal and you'll have leftovers for a week.
holy portions batman ... excellent !!
ALWAYS the best food, our favorite restaurant! Authentic Italian flavors. Great service!
Good food. Nothing special though.
The mushroom ravioli is amazing!
Great food and quick service. Appetizers were so good.

I've known this spot for years now. It's incredible to think how fast time has gone by. It's still my favorite Italian joint. There's just something about it as soon as you step inside the building. Great ambience, friendly staff, and the GM is an incredible guy. The food is excellent, the kitchen staff really deserve all the credit here. Huge portion sizes, and it's the perfect place for family gatherings...and even better for that first date with a special someone. If you haven't already, give this place a shot. You won't regret it.
Even though we had reservations for 9pm, we got quality service. Just a little more seasoning would have made my chicken parmesan perfect. Definitely going back.
Awesome food!
Large meals, nice atmosphere. Great, if you're into that sort of thing.
Exceptional service...the graduation dinner was perfect!

The waitress was prompt and delivered great customer service. I had the shrimp scampi and the sauce was very watered down. The lasagna was bland and my daughter liked the spaghetti! The atmosphere is great but I was expecting more authenticity from this Italian place. If the chef turns the flavor up a notch it would be a great place! Add more garlic and pesto to your dishes and vino!
My first time here and it was fabulous!
Very good food.
Food is great. Parking is a challenge
Really good place, very tasty food!
Had a great dinner of salad & pasta. Dana was awesome and Micheal was a great server. We will be back!

Our server was Alex was AMAZING! The food was good. The restaurant is Nice. Half off wine Monday, and half off appetizer Tuesday. We had a good time. It was a wonderful experience. Good prices with huge portions. I ordered half portion and I had more for dinner the next day. Will be back!😊
The food last week was awesome and my mother was very excited about the restaurant which was her first time. Excellent food and customer service

Ordered the half order of baked ziti(which was so good) and it came in a plate the size of a serving platter. Took half of it home. As I said it was delicious and very reasonably priced. I will definitely be going back. If you want pizza or some other fast food concoction go elsewhere, this is genuine italiano at its finest. The Bolognese sauce is wonderful. I highly recommend it.
Customer service was good, but there is an odor think the carpet need to be replaced.  Could not enjoy my food.
The tried really hard to accommodate our vegan needs.
Not a bad place for a meal in town.

Fabulous Italian food in a friendly environment. Huge portions, but don't miss the garlic bread. Festive atmosphere, very friendly and attentive service. Will definitely be our go-to place before shows at the Aurora Theatre.
Very delicious!!
I love this place. They have very good food and service. The ambiance is lovely. Great date place.
Delish

So I finally went into Dominick’s after my friend wouldn’t stop telling me how I needed to try the food here. I was so pleased with how great the service is as well as the food! My server Kim was knowledgeable and so helpful. I had the tortellini & roasted chicken as my entree and the calamari to start. The chicken was succulent and I even had plenty to take home. The Portion sizes are more than generous! I was truly amazed at the service and environment of this restaurant. It has a cool relaxing Italian jazzy vibe to it. I made plans to go back on  Fri. 03/22 , and i went on Sat. 03/16/ lol! You all enjoy!
We really enjoy this restaurant! The staff are very experienced, knowledgeable of their dishes and friendly. Enjoy!!
Fantastic food! Beautiful building.
The dish I had was really good not a fan of the ambiance.
Great food and atmosphere.

Had a reservation at 5:30. Arrived on time. Restaurant half full. After a little confusion we were seated and then promptly ignored for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, people are coming in after us, getting seated and served.  Four to five servers are standing around chatting with each other, walking past our table. No one stopped to take a drink order or a food order. Nothing. Like we were invisible. We left. I spoke with the manager who was indifferent to the whole experience. Other than saying, "sorry" he didn't say or do anything to get us to stay or come back. No promise of a discount on a future meal. Something. Anything. Got nothing. They didn't care from the manager on down. We left and called Longhorn. Call ahead seating. We arrived, were seated in a couple of minutes and promptly served. Wow. What a difference.

Dinner here was great. My wife and I enjoyed a delicious dinner with great service. The fare was tasty traditional Italian, in large portions. Our waitress said that the "half" potion entrees would serve up to two, I was a little incredulous. I guess I *could* have finished my chicken parmesana, but eating half and taking the outer half home still left me satisfied. The bread and side of pasta with Alfredo sauce completed a great meal. I could take the wife again and we could share a half size entree, and still have plenty, which would actually make a pretty cheap date meal.

Hello,  I could not wait to get home to type my experience at Dominicks -Lawrenceville location.  Initially my sister and I came in search to find venue for my sons future graduation party.   The welcoming  service received from Dana and staff ( Stephanie ) was so warm and inviting I wanted to seal the deal that very moment.  I was so motivated I momentarily forget that I needed to consult with my husband . Nonetheless, this location is a very close contender due to the wonderful service. It Is hard these days , to feel welcomed , invited and wanted. Many businesses have lost the art of customer service. That’s not the case of Dominick’s we will be back, hopefully regularly.

Took my fiancee here for Valentine's Day and the food was excellent. The carpet was noticeably stained in the back where we sat. Our waitress was a little attitudinal when my lady said it was cold in the restaurant(It was cold). The waitress said she wished it was cold. I can't remember her name but she didn't have any teeth.  We'll be back in the spring because of the food.
First time there with my husband on Valentine's Day great food and great service
Nice place
Awesome!
Amazing....with huge portions

Me and my wife went to dinner. My wife wanted Olive Garden I said we should check out this place.  I was a chef for 12 years and hate blasting restaurants but honestly the apathetic execution is forcing me to do this. I normally pay my bill, tip, and don’t come back.  It was Friday and service was not necessarily slow but more so clunky and focused on money rather than experience.  We ordered the cheese garlic bread. Timing was fine but they put garlic chips on a loaf of bread and covered it in oil and cheese and broiled it... the idea seemed great but the amount of garlic was offensive, I don’t think we have ever had left over garlic bread.  I ordered the chicken Alfredo the wife ordered the mushroom ravioli. I feel like it took 3 or 4 minutes to come out, which is not a good thing.  Sauce was runny, the texture of the chicken was precooked and flavorless, and I can get over the chopped up tomatoes (shouldn’t be there but don’t taste like much) but the huge amount of basil(shouldn’t be there and don’t taste good in Alfredo) in the Alfredo made me stop eating after a few bites. By the way the menu didn’t mention basil but did say there would be fried spinach to garnish which were not present.  The mushroom raviolis weren’t very good. It was really disheveled, and just forgetful.  We got the half portions, which were about the normal cost of a full portion at a normal restaurant and they were huge.  It took almost 20 minutes after we stopped eating to be able to pay.

So my fiance and I went to this restaurant a few days ago for a date night, something we don't do often. We were also scouting possible locations for our engagement party, and Dominick's was near the top of that list. It had all the qualifications, it was an Italian restaurant, it looked like it had a private room for special occasions, and it was a bit more high class than Olive Garden. Sadly, the food did remind me of that mediocre restaurant chain. I ordered ravioli, and it literally had more cheese on it, than in it. My fiance ordered spicy chicken and sausage pasta, because she enjoys and often eats spicy food. But not this time, she took about half a dozen bites and couldn't take it anymore. Our waitress, although sweet, always seemed to be in a rush for us to order, and pressured us into ordering alcohol. We really wanted to give this place one last chance, as we had such high hopes for it, so we ordered a cannoli for dessert, which was also not exceptional. If I had ordered this meal at Olive Garden for $50 I would have been satisfied, but not $75 at a privately own Italian restaurant. Needless to say, this won't be the location of our engagement party.
